label: adherens junction
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of two outer epidermal cells of the pharynx. There is an adherens junction (arrowheads) between two cells. Scale bar is 0.5 um.

label: pharynx longitudinal muscle cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of a transverse section through the pharynx. The inner longitudinal muscle (arrowheads) is immediately deep to the inner circular muscle of the pharynx. Magenta = circular; green = longitudinal; red = radial. Scale bar is 2 um.

label: pharynx radial muscle cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of a transverse section through the pharynx. Immediately deep to the inner epithelial layer of the pharynx is musculature that has been colored. Magenta = circular; blue = longitudinal; yellow = radial. Scale bar is 5 um.

label: anterior region of trunk fragment
comment: Illustration of the anterior region of a trunk fragment (green).

label: excretory cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph showing a cell that is part of the collecting duct. An arrowhead marks the nucleus of this cell. Note the visible lumen of the collecting duct extending out and passing through the basal lamina. This cell is involved in excretion. Scale bar is 2 um.

label: ventral region of the whole animal
comment: Illustration of the ventral region of the whole animal (in green).

label: ventral region of trunk fragment
comment: Illustration of the ventral region of a trunk fragment (green).

label: posterior primary gut branch
comment: Depicted by field contains hematoxylin and eosin staining section of a asexual adult animal. The posterior primary gut branch is indicated by arrows. Scale bar = 250um

label: protonephridia
comment: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/Depicted by field contains a whole-mount acetylated tubulin (AcTub) staining. Scale bars_ 500 um. Inset to right shows depth-coded projection of AcTub staining. Superficial structures are in blue and deeper structures are in red. Scale bars: 50 um

label: circular muscle cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting the body wall musculature beneath the dorsal epidermis. The first layer of muscle cells beneath the basal lamina (BL), circular muscle, have been colored and labeled with arrowheads. Circular muscle = magenta; longitudinal muscle = green; diagonal muscle = red. Scale bar is 2um.

label: prepharyngeal region
comment: Depicted by field contains diagram representation of body region.

label: nuclear envelope
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting the nuclear envelope (arrowheads). The nucleus takes up the top left corner of the image and the nuclear envelope encloses it. Scale bar is 200 nm.

label: ventral region of posterior fragment
comment: Illustration of the ventral region of a posterior fragment (green).

label: secondary gut branch
comment: Depicted by field contains hematoxylin and eosin staining section of a asexual adult animal. The secondary gut branch is indicated by arrows. Scale bar = 250um

label: Stage 6
comment: Depicted by field contains hematoxylin and eosin staining section of a stage 6 embryo. Scale bar = 100um

label: nuclear inner membrane
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting the nuclear envelope. The nucleus takes up the top left corner of the image and the inner nuclear membrane has been labeled with arrowheads. Scale bar is 200 nm.

label: posterior region of prepharyngeal fragment
comment: Illustration of the posterior region of a prepharyngeal fragment (green).

label: ventral region of postpharyngeal fragment
comment: Illustration of the ventral region of a postpharyngeal fragment (green).

label: pharynx outer nerve plexus
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of a transverse section through the pharynx.The pharynx pouch cavity is at the top.  The outer nerve plexus (arrowheads) is immediately deep to the outer circular muscle of the pharynx. Red = circular; blue = longitudinal. Scale bar is 2 um.

label: thick fragment
comment: Illustration of a thick fragment (in green).

label: mitochondrion
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting a couple different cells. A few mitochondria have been labeled with arrowheads. Note the variation in shape from spherical to rod-like. This is dependent on cutting orientation at fission/fusion state of the mitochondria. Scale bar is 1 um.

label: collecting duct epithelial cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph showing a cell (outlined) that is part of the collecting duct. Note how much more stained this cell is, compared to the surrounding ones. Also note the visible lumen of the collecting duct inside the cell where it is white and wrinkled. Scale bar is 1um.

label: posterior pole
comment: Illustration of the posterior pole (in green).

label: lysosome
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting two lysosomes (arrowheads) within a cell. The nucleus sits in the bottom left corner. Lysosomes can sometimes be identified by the swirling material they are breaking down inside. Scale bar is 0.5um.

label: pharynx inner epithelium surface
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of a transverse section through the pharynx. An epidermal cell, a part of the inner epithelial layer, has been marked with arrowheads. Immediately deep to the inner epithelial layer of the pharynx is musculature that has been colored. Magenta = circular; blue = longitudinal; yellow = radial. Scale bar is 5 um.

label: longitudinal region
comment: Illustration of a longitudinal region (green).

label: adult hermaphrodite
comment: Depcited by field shows a light microscopy image of a sexually mature adult with a scale bar of 2 mm.

label: posterior region of tail fragment
comment: Illustration of the posterior region of a tail  fragment (green).

label: ventral region of longitudinal fragment
comment: Illustration of the ventral region of a longitudinal fragment (green).

label: posterior region of anterior fragment
comment: Illustration of the posterior region of an anterior fragment (green).

label: chromosome arm
comment: Image is an electron micrograph showing a mitotic cell. An arrowhead marks the long arm of a chromosome. Scale bar is 1um.

label: Stage 3
comment: Depicted by field contains hematoxylin and eosin staining section of a stage 3 embryo. Scale bar = 100um

label: ventral region of tail fragment
comment: Illustration of the ventral region of a tail fragment (green).

label: asexual adult
comment: Depicted by field shows an asexual adult with a scale bar of 500um

label: pharynx pouch epithelium
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of a transverse slice through the parapharyngeal region. It includes the dorsal epidermis, pharynx pouch epithelium (arrowheads), and a portion of the pharynx. Dorsal is up and the lumen of the pouch is visible as the white stripe in the middle of the micrograph. Scale bar is 5um.

label: plug amputation
comment: Illustration of an example of a plug amputation showing resultant fragment and donor wound.

label: dorsal region of head fragment
comment: Illustration of the dorsal region of a head fragment (green).

label: posterior region of postpharyngeal fragment
comment: Illustration of the posterior region of a postpharyngeal fragment (green).

label: oral hemisphere
comment: Illustration of the oral hemispshere (in green).

label: dorsal region of the whole animal
comment: Illustration of the dorsal region of the whole animal (in green).

label: anterior region of posterior fragment
comment: Illustration of the anterior region of a posterior fragment (green).

label: dorsal region of posterior fragment
comment: Illustration of the dorsal region of a posterior fragment (green).

label: copulatory region
comment: Depicted by field contains diagram representation of body region.

label: lipid droplet
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting two lipid droplets (arrowheads) within two different cells. Note the mostly round shape of the droplets. Often, mitochondria can be seen clumped around lipids. Scale bar is 1um.

label: wedge wound
comment: Illustration of a wedge wound.

label: Smed asexual biotype
comment: Image is an scanning electron micrograph of the dorsal side of an entire animal. This is an adult asexual Schmidtea mediterranea. Anterior is to the right and posterior is to the left. Scale bar is 500um.

label: anterior region of head fragment
comment: Illustration of the anterior region of a head fragment (green).

label: muscle cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting a muscle cell (arrowheads) cut in a transverse orientation with respect to the fiber length. Note the texture of the cytoplasm that comes from the organization of myofibrils. Scale bar is 1um.

label: medial muscle cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting multiple medial dorsal-ventral muscle cells (arrowheads). At the bottom of this image is the ventral epidermi, to the left is the dark staining of the gut tissue. Scale bar is 10um.

label: anterior-posterior axis of the whole animal
comment: Depiction shows an asexual adult with the term annotated in yellow. Scale bar =500um

label: extracellular matrix
comment: Image is an electron micrograph showing the extracellular matrix (arrowheads) between two cells. Scale bar is 0.2um.

label: medial-lateral axis of the whole animal
comment: Depiction shows an asexual adult with the term annotated in yellow. Scale bar =500um

label: Stage 8
comment: Depicted by field contains hematoxylin and eosin staining section of a stage 8 embryo. Scale bar = 100um

label: nuclear outer membrane
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting the nuclear envelope. The nucleus takes up the top left corner of the image and the outer nuclear membrane has been labeled with arrowheads. Scale bar is 200 nm.

label: dorsal region of plug fragment
comment: Illustration of the dorsal region of a plug fragment (green).

label: pharynx inner circular muscle cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of a transverse section through the pharynx. The pharynx lumen it to the left. The inner circular muscle (arrowheads) is immediately deep to the inner epithelial layer of the pharynx. Magenta = circular; green = longitudinal; red = radial. Scale bar is 2 um.

label: ventral region of plug fragment
comment: Illustration of the ventral region of a plug fragment (green).

label: ventral region of plug fragment
comment: Illustration of the ventral region of a plug fragment (green).

label: mucus
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of the outside of an animal at the marginal adhesive zone. The adhesive papilla are colored in blue and surround each secretory pore (yellow). Mucus (arrowheads) and cilia are both green. Scale bar is 2um.

label: chromatoid body
comment: Image is an electron micrograph showing a chromatoid body (arrowhead) next to the cell's nucleus (N) which takes up the bottom left corner. Scale bar is 200nm.

label: ventral region of lateral fragment
comment: Illustration of the ventral region of a lateral fragment (green).

label: distal tubule
comment: Depicted by field contains a diagram representing the protonephrida unit (top) as well as a 3D rendering of confocal data depicting the same. In the diagram, terminal flame cells and their corresponding cilia are in blues, the proximal tubule is in reds, the distal tubule is in greens while thecollecting duct is in purple. In the 3D rendering below the cilia (AcTub) are in blue, portions of the proximal tubule (slc6a-13) are in red while the distal tubule (slc6a-12) is in green.

label: posterior region of posterior fragment
comment: Illustration of the posterior region of a posterior fragment (green).

label: basal lamina of epidermis
comment: Image is an electron micrograph showing the dorsal epidermis. Epidermal cells can be seen above (superfical to) the basal lamina (BL) and the body wall musculature can be seen below. Scale bar is 2um.

label: ciliated epithelium
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of an outer epidermal cell of the pharynx. These cells are heavily ciliated. Scale bar is 2um.

label: pharynx pouch epithelial surface
comment: The depicted by field is a hemotoxylin and eosin stained coronal section encompassing the pharynx and surrounding tissues. Anterior is up. The parapharyngeal pouch surface is marked by black arrows. Scale bar is 200um.

label: anterior region of postpharyngeal fragment
comment: Illustration of the anterior region of a postpharyngeal fragment (green).

label: enteric musculature
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting the enteric musculature (arrowheads) surrounding the gut, which extends across the top of the image. These cells are very small compared to the layer of medial muscle underneath them. Scale bar is 1um.

label: ventral midline
comment: Illustration of the ventral midline (in green).

label: secretory pore
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of a viscid gland cell passing across the basal lamina (BL). This cell secretes a specialized type of mucus. The secretory duct transports mucus to the outside of the animal, through the secretory pore (arrowhead). Ventral is down and scale bar is 5um.

label: proximal-distal axis of the whole animal
comment: Pharynx of an asexual adult exposed by tricaine treatment. The proximodistal axis is denoted with the double headed magenta arrow.

label: adhesive papilla
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of the outside of an animal at the marginal adhesive zone. The adhesive papilla (arrowheads) are colored in blue and surround each secretory pore (yellow). Mucus and cilia are both green. Scale bar is 2um.

label: pharynx inner nerve plexus
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of a transverse section through the pharynx. Neuronal cells/tissue are marked with arrowheads. The inner nerve plexus is immediately deep to the inner longitudinal musculature. Magenta = circular; blue = longitudinal; yellow = radial. Scale bar is 5 um.

label: pharynx inner epidermal cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of a transverse section through the pharynx. The phayrnx lumen is to the bottom left. An epidermal cell, a part of the inner epithelial layer, has been marked with arrowheads. Immediately deep to the inner epithelial layer of the pharynx is musculature that has been colored. Magenta = circular; blue = longitudinal; yellow = radial. Scale bar is 5 um.

label: adhesion gland
comment: Image is an electron micrograph showing the multicellular total adhesion gland structure (outlined) embedded in the epidermis. Note that the gland cells cross the basal lamina into the epithelium. Ventral is up and scale bar is 2um.

label: epidermal rhabdite
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting the epidermis.  Rhabdites (arrowheads) can be seen in various stages of expansion inside of the epidermal cells. Scale bar is 5 um.

label: pharynx lumen
comment: Depicted by field contains hematoxylin and eosin staining section of a asexual adult animal. Cavity of pharynx is indicated by arrows. Scale bar = 250um

label: pharynx outer epidermal cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of a transverse section through the pharynx. The pharynx pouch cavity is at the top. An epidermal cell, a part of the outer epithelium, has been labeled with arrowheads. Immediately deep to the outer epithelial layer of the pharynx is musculature that has been colored. Red = circular; blue = longitudinal. Scale bar is 2 um.

label: secretory cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of a viscid gland cell (arrowheads) passing across the basal lamina (BL). This cell secretes a specialized type of mucus. The secretory duct transports mucus to the outside of the animal, through the secretory pore. Ventral is down and scale bar is 5um.

label: ventral region of head fragment
comment: Illustration of the ventral region of a head fragment (green).

label: nuclear pore
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting the nuclear envelope. The nucleus takes up the top left corner of the image and two nuclear pores have been labeled with arrowheads. Scale bar is 200 nm.

label: dorsal-ventral muscle cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting multiple dorsal-ventral muscle cells (arrowheads).  The ventral epidermis is at the bottom of this image. Scale bar is 10um.

label: cytoplasm
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting a portion of a cell. Outside of the nucleus (N), the arrowheads mark areas of cytoplasm, which appears as a mottled gray filling. Scale bar is 0.5um.

label: head region
comment: Depicted by field contains diagram representation of body region.

label: Stage 5
comment: Depicted by field contains hematoxylin and eosin staining section of a stage 5 embryo. Scale bar = 100um

label: inner zone of gland cells
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting a transverse section through the pharynx. Arrowheads label the inner zone of gland cells. They can be identified by the mucus granules the cell body is filled with. Scale bar is 5um.

label: septate junction
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting the inner epithelium of the pharynx. Septate junctions (arrowheads) can be clearly seen between cells. Scale bar is 200 nm.

label: axon
comment: Image is an electron micrograph showing a cross section of an axon (arrowheads), right underneath or medial to the dorsal body wall musculature. Dorsal is up and the scale bar is 2um.

label: viscid gland cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph showing the whole adhesion gland structure, specifically outlining a single cell (viscid gland cell) associated with this multicelluar structure. Ventral is up and scale bar is 2um.

label: posterior region of lateral fragment
comment: Illustration of the posterior region of a lateral fragment (green).

label: dorsal region of plug fragment
comment: Illustration of the dorsal region of a plug fragment (green).

label: dorsal region of lateral fragment
comment: Illustration of the dorsal region of a lateral fragment (green).

label: cell-cell adhesion
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of two outer epidermal cells of the pharynx. There is an adherens junction (arrowheads) between two cells. Scale bar is 0.5 um.

label: nucleus
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of several nuclei (N) close to and a part of the dorsal epidermis. Note how the epidermal cell nuclei appear more wrinkled and have stained differently than the cells lying beneath the basal lamina (BL). Scale bar is 2 um.

label: flame bulb
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting a flame cell (outlined), which is a part of the flame bulb. "N" marks this cell's nucleus and the cilia are noted by an arrowhead. Scale bar is 1um.

label: left-right axis of the whole animal
comment: Depiction shows an asexual adult with the term annotated in yellow. Scale bar =500um

label: chromosome
comment: Image is an electron micrograph showing a mitotic cell. An arrowhead marks the long arm of a chromosome. Scale bar is 1um.

label: chromatin
comment: Image is an electron micrograph showing a mitotic cell with condensed chromatin (arrowhead). Scale bar is 1um.

label: dorsal midline
comment: Illustration of the dorsal midline (in green).

label: mouth
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of the mouth (arrowheads), which is located on the ventral side of the animal. Note the heavily ciliated pharynx that is peeking out. Scale bar is 10um.

label: parapharyngeal region
comment: Depicted by field contains diagram representation of body region.

label: adenal rhabdite
comment: Image is an electron micrograph showing the dorsal epidermis and underlying basal lamina at the top. Adenal rhabdites are marked with "Rh" and can be seen in cells underneath or medial to the basal lamina. Scale bar is 2um.

label: pharynx inner longitudinal muscle cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of a transverse section through the pharynx. The inner longitudinal muscle (arrowheads) is immediately deep to the inner circular muscle of the pharynx. Magenta = circular; green = longitudinal; red = radial. Scale bar is 2 um.

label: secretory vesicle
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting two golgi bodies and accompanying secratory vesicles. A few have been labeled with arrowheads. Scale bar is 200 nm.

label: gland cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting a portion of a gland cell (arrowheads). Note the nucleus surrounded by endoplasmic reticulum and the dark mucus granules that fill the long cytoplasmic projection. Scale bar is 2 um.

label: epithelium
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of a transverse section of a planarian through the pharyngeal region depicting 3 different epithelial layers (arrowheads). At the top is the dorsal epidermis, in the middle is the epithelium of the pharyngeal pouch, and at the bottom of the image, the outer epithelium of the pharynx. Scale bar is 5um.

label: pharynx outer circular muscle cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of a transverse section through the pharynx. The pharynx pouch cavity is at the top. The outer circular muscle (arrowheads) is immediately deep to the outer longitudinal muscle of the pharynx. Red = circular; blue = longitudinal. Scale bar is 2 um.

label: ventral region of prepharyngeal fragment
comment: Illustration of the ventral region of a prepharyngeal fragment (green).

label: goblet cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph showing part of the gastrodermis. A goblet cell, a type of gastrodermal cell is labeled with arrowheads. Note the large, dark mucus granules contained in the cell body. The lumen of the gut can be seen on the right side of the image and has been labeled with "L." Scale bar is 1 um.

label: wedge amputation
comment: Illustration of a wedge amputation depicting the resultant donor wound and wedge fragment.

label: secretory duct
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of a viscid gland cell passing across the basal lamina (BL). This cell secretes a specialized type of mucus. The secretory duct (arrowhead) transports mucus to the outside of the animal, through the secretory pore. Ventral is down and scale bar is 5um.

label: pharynx tip
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of the tip of the pharynx. Many gland cells can be seen inside, filled with mucus. Scale bar is 5um.

label: intracellular granule
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting a cell with many intracellular granules (arrowheads) visible in the cytoplasm. The scale bar is 1um.

label: endoplasmic reticulum
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting endoplasmic reticulum (magenta) in multiple cells. Scale bar is 0.5um.

label: anterior region of prepharyngeal fragment
comment: Illustration of the anterior region of a prepharyngeal fragment (green).

label: proximal tubule
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting a proximal tubule (arrowheads) of the protonephridia structure. Note the cilia and the characteristic way the cell membrane connects with other proximal tubule epithelial cells. Scale bar is 2um.

label: thin fragment
comment: Illustration of a thin fragment (in green).

label: auricle
comment: Image is a scanning electron micrograph of the dorsal side of the head of an adult worm. The auricles (arrowheads) appear as a short groove on each side of the head. Anteror is down and scale bar is 100um.

label: rough endoplasmic reticulum
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting the rough endoplasmic reticulum (arrowheads) of a cell. Ribosomes can be seen associating with the ER membrane creating a rough ER, as well as  free within the cytoplasm of the cell. Scale bar is 200 nm.

label: dorsal region of postpharyngeal fragment
comment: Illustration of the dorsal region of a postpharyngeal fragment (green).

label: rhabdite
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting the epidermis. Inside of the epidermal cells, rhabdites (arrowheads) can be seen in various stages of expansion. Scale bar is 5 um.

label: tail tip
comment: Illustration of the tail tip (in green).

label: anterior region of plug fragment
comment: Illustration of the anterior region of a plug fragment (green).

label: tertiary gut branch
comment: Depicted by field contains hematoxylin and eosin staining section of a asexual adult animal. The tertiary gut branch indicated is by arrows. Scale bar = 250um

label: epidermal cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting the dorsal epidermis. A single cell has been labeled with arrowheads. Immediately deep to the epidermis is the basal lamina, labeled with "BL." Scale bar is 2um.

label: marginal adhesive zone
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting the lateral dorsoventral boundary. Several adhesion gland cells have been labeled with arrowheads to visualize the line of the marginal adhesive zone. Scale bar is 10um.

label: microvillus
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting a portion of the outer epithelium of the pharynx. Microvilli  on the left hand of the image have been labeled with arrowheads. To the right of the microvilli are larger cilia. Note the difference in width and length. Scale bar is 2 um.

label: ribosome
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting ribosomes (arrowheads) in two separate cells. They can be seen as small dots in the cytoplasm and associating with the rough endoplasmic reticulum in the cell in the bottom of the micrograph. Scale bar is 200 nm.

label: pharynx outer epithelium surface
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of a transverse section through the pharynx. The pharynx pouch cavity is at the top. The outer epithelium has been labeled with arrowheads. Immediately deep to the outer epithelial layer of the pharynx is musculature that has been colored. Red = circular; blue = longitudinal. Scale bar is 2 um.

label: nephridiopore
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting a collecting duct (arrowheads) passing through the basal lamina (BL). Dorsal is up and the scale bar is 5 um.

label: posterior region of wedge fragment
comment: Illustration of the posterior region of a wedge fragment (green).

label: posterior region of longitudinal fragment
comment: Illustration of the posterior region of a longitudinal fragment (green).

label: post-blastema region
comment: Illustration of the post-blastema region(in green) in the anterior region of a regenerating tail fragment.

label: anchor cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph showing the total multicellualr adhesion gland structure. The anchor cell has been outlined, though mucus-filled projections of gland cells can be seen densely packed inside. Nucleus is that of the anchor cell. Ventral is up and scale bar is 2um.

label: glial cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting a section of the ventral nerve cord. The arrowheads point at a likely glial cell. Note the difference in darkness of cytoplasm in the cell body of  the glial cell compared to the surrounding axons. Scale bar is 2um.

label: visceral musculature
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting the visceral musculature (arrowheads) that lies beneath the gut. The gut is identifiable by the collection of darkly stained lipid droplets in the top right corner and the white of the lumen at the top of the image. Scale bar is 10um

label: body wall musculature
comment: http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/Image is an electron micrograph of the dorsal epidermis, basal lamina (BL), and underlying body wall musculature. Three types of muscle cells have been color coded form superficial to deep_ Circular muscle = magenta; longitudinal muscle = green; diagonal muscle = red. Scale bar is 2um.

label: pharynx pouch cavity
comment: Depicted by field contains hematoxylin and eosin stainingcoronal section section of a asexual adult animal. Parapharyngeal pouch cavity is indicated by arrows. Scale bar = 250um

label: embryonic wall
comment: Depicted by field contains hematoxylin and eosin staining section of a stage 5 embryo with anatomical feature noted with black indicators.

label: Stage 4
comment: Depicted by field contains hematoxylin and eosin staining section of a stage 4 embryo. Scale bar = 100um

label: apical surface of the epidermis
comment: Electron micrograph of the dorsal epidermis in a transverse plane from an asexual adult animal. The apical epidermis surface is noted with magenta arrows. Scale bar is 5um.

label: gastrodermis surface
comment: The depicted by field is a hemotoxylin and eosin stained coronal section encompassing the anterior primary gut branch. The lumen gut surface is marked by black arrows. Scale bar is 200um.

label: longitudinal muscle cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting the body wall musculature beneath the dorsal epidermis. The longitudinal muscle cells (arrowheads) sit behind both the circular muscle and the diagonal muscle. Circular muscle = magenta; longitudinal muscle = green; diagonal muscle = red. Scale bar is 2um.

label: cell-cell junction
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of two outer epidermal cells of the pharynx. There is an adherens junction (arrowheads) between two cells. Scale bar is 0.5 um.

label: axoneme
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of several cilia where a cross-section reveals the axoneme with a 9+2 arrangement of microtubles. Arrowheads denote microtubules. Scale bar is 100nm.

label: anterior region of tail fragment
comment: Illustration of the anterior region of a tail fragment (green).

label: plasma membrane
comment: Image is an electron micrograph showing several cells. Arrowheads label the plasma membrane, the boundary between cells. Scale bar is 1um.

label: ventral region of anterior fragment
comment: Illustration of the ventral region of an anterior fragment (green).

label: Golgi apparatus
comment: Image is an electron micrograph showing golgi bodies (arrowheads). Many secretory vesicles can be seen, as well as rough endoplasmic reticulum on the right side of the micrograph. Scale bar is 0.2 um.

label: dorsal region of prepharyngeal fragment
comment: Illustration of the dorsal region of a prepharyngeal fragment (green).

label: posterior region of plug fragment
comment: Illustration of the posterior region of a plug fragment (green).

label: digestive tract lumen
comment: Depicted by field contains hematoxylin and eosin staining on a coronal section of a asexual adult animal. The lumen of the digestive tract is indicated by arrows. Scale bar = 250um

label: dorsal region of the epidermis
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting the dorsal epidermis (arrowheads). Also visible in this micrograph, immediately deep to the epidermis is the basal lamina and beneath that is a photoreceptor. Scale bar is 10 um.

label: anterior region of the whole animal
comment: Illustration of the anterior region of the whole animal (in green).

label: Stage 2
comment: Depicted by field contains hematoxylin and eosin staining section of a stage 2 embryo. Scale bar = 100um

label: diagonal muscle cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting the body wall musculature beneath the dorsal epidermis. The third layer of cells beneath the basement membrane, diagonal muscle cells, have been colored and labeled with arrowheads. Circular muscle = magenta; longitudinal muscle = green; diagonal muscle = red. Scale bar is 2um.

label: anterior region of wedge fragment
comment: Illustration of the anterior region of a wedge fragment (green).

label: plug wound
comment: Illustration of a wound left in a donor animal resulting from a plug amputation.

label: pharynx inner epithelium
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of a transverse section through the pharynx. An epidermal cell, a part of the inner epithelial layer, has been marked with arrowheads. Immediately deep to the inner epithelial layer of the pharynx is musculature that has been colored. Magenta = circular; blue = longitudinal; yellow = radial. Scale bar is 5 um.

label: dorsal region of tail
comment: Illustration of the dorsal region of the tail (in green).

label: proximal tubule epithelial cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of a proximal tubule epithelial cell (arrowheads). N = nucleus. Note the way the cell is wrapped around the cilia, creating the lumen in the middle. Scale bar is 2um.

label: basal surface of the epidermis
comment: Electron micrograph of the dorsal epidermis in a transverse plane. The basal epidermis surface is noted with magenta arrows. Scale bar is 5um.

label: posterior region of the whole animal
comment: Illustration of the posterior compartement of the whole animal (in green).

label: nucleolus
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting a nucleus. Inside, the nucleolus has been labeled with arrowheads. Scale bar is 1 um.

label: basal body
comment: Image is an electron micrograph showing a cross-section of a cilium, revealing the basal body (arrowhead). Scale bar is 0.5um.

label: dorsal region of tail fragment
comment: Illustration of the dorsal region of a tail fragment (green).

label: Stage 7
comment: Depicted by field contains hematoxylin and eosin staining section of a stage 7 embryo. Scale bar = 100um

label: non ciliated epithelial cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of the dorsal side of the animal where there is a transition from nonciliated epidermal cells to ciliated ones. On the left side of the image are the ciliated cells and on the right are the nonciliated. A few nonciliated have been marked with arrowheads. Scale bar is 10um.

label: neoblast
comment: Image is an electron micrograph showing a neoblast undergoing mitotic telophase (outlined). The condensed chromatin is visible toward the left side of the cell and has been outlined by the nuclear envelope. Scale bar is 1um.

label: flame cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting a flame cell (outlined), which is a part of the flame bulb. "N" marks this cell's nucleus and the cilia are noted by an arrowhead. Scale bar is 1um.

label: dorsal region of anterior fragment
comment: Illustration of the dorsal region of an anterior fragment (green).

label: anterior pole
comment: Illustration of the anterior pole (green).

label: anterior region of longitudinal fragment
comment: Illustration of the anterior region of a longitudinal fragment (green).

label: pharynx epithelium
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of a transverse section through the pharynx. Outlined, is the outer epithium, which is an "insunk" epithelium where the nuclei are set back medially away from the epithelium surface. Here, just the surface is outlined.. Scale bar is 2um.

label: anterior primary gut branch
comment: Depicted by field contains hematoxylin and eosin staining section of a asexual adult animal. Anterior primary gut branch indicated by arrows. Scale bar = 250um

label: anterior tip
comment: Illustration of the anterior tip in green.

label: tail region
comment: Depicted by field contains diagram representation of body region.

label: Smed sexual biotype
comment: Depicted by field contains light micrscope image of asexual and sexual biotypes of Schmidtea meditteranea with their respective karyotypes. Note that the asexual bioptype has a chromosome inversion compared to the sexual.

label: ER membrane
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting (rough) endoplasmic reticulum adjacent tp the nucleus (N). The arrowheads mark the ER membrane. Note the ribosomes (small dots) that can be seen both in the cytoplasm and lining the ER membrane. Scale bar is 0.2um.

label: glycogen granule
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting glycogen granules (arrowheads) within the cytoplasm of a cell. Scale bar is 200 nm.

label: dorsal stripe
comment: Image is an electron micrograph showing the dorsal side of the head of an adult worm. Arrowheads mark where the ciliated cells of the dorsal stripe can be seen. Anterior is up and scale bar is 100um.

label: anterior region of lateral fragment
comment: Illustration of the anterior region of a lateral fragment (green).

label: dorsal region of trunk fragment
comment: Illustration of the dorsal region of a trunk fragment (green).

label: releasing gland cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph showing the whole adhesion gland structure. Arrowheads mark releasing gland cells which are associated with this multicelluar structure. The releasing gland cells have very small excretory particles compared to the neighboring viscid gland. Ventral is up and scale bar is 1um.

label: posterior region of trunk fragment
comment: Illustration of the posterior region of a trunk fragment (green).

label: collecting duct
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting a collecting duct (arrowheads) passing through the basal lamina (BL). Dorsal is up and the scale bar is 5 um.

label: sagittal plane of the whole animal
comment: Illustration of a sagittal plane of the whole animal (in green).

label: pharynx outer longitudinal muscle cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of a transverse section through the pharynx. The pharynx pouch cavity is at the top. The outer longitudinal muscle (arrowheads) is immediately deep to the outer epithelium of the pharynx. Red = circular; blue = longitudinal. Scale bar is 2 um.

label: distal tubule epithelial cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph showing a cell (outlined) that is part of the collecting duct. Note how much more stained this cell is, compared to the surrounding ones. Also note the visible lumen of the collecting duct inside the cell where it is white and wrinkled. Scale bar is 1um.

label: oral-aboral axis of the embryo
comment: Illustration noting the oral-aboral axis in cyan double headed arrow.  It starts at the embryonic pharynx and extends to opposite pole.

label: dorsal region of longitudinal fragment
comment: Illustration of the dorsal region of a longitudinal fragment (green).

label: Hyman vesicle
comment: Image is an immunoelectron micrograph depicting hyman vesicles in the apical side of an epidermal cell. Scale bar is 1um.

label: anterior region of anterior fragment
comment: Illustration of the anterior region of an anterior fragment (green).

label: pharynx circular muscle cell
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of a transverse section through the pharynx. The pharynx lumen it to the left. The inner circular muscle (arrowheads) is immediately deep to the inner epithelial layer of the pharynx. Magenta = circular; green = longitudinal; red = radial. Scale bar is 2 um.

label: cell junction
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of two outer epidermal cells of the pharynx. There is an adherens junction (arrowheads) between two cells. Scale bar is 0.5 um.

label: cilium
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting several cilia (arrowheads) emerging from a ventral epidermis cell. Scale bar is 0.5um.

label: posterior region of head fragment
comment: Illustration of the posterior region of a head fragment (green).

label: midline
comment: Illustration of the midline (in green).

label: smooth endoplasmic reticulum
comment: Image is an electron micrograph depicting smooth ER (arrowheads) in a cell, next to the nucleus (N). Ribosomes can be seen within the cytoplasm, but not associating with the ER membrane. Scale bar is 200 nm.

label: parenchymal musculature
comment: Image is an electron micrograph of the parenchyma. Three muscle cells have been notated with an arrowhead. Scale bar is 2 um.
